<section id="texify">

<?dbhh topicname="MIKTEXHELP_TEXIFY" topicid="0"?>

<title>&texify;</title>

<simplesect>

<title>Synopsis</title>

<cmdsynopsis>
&texify;
<arg><option>-@</option></arg>
<group>
<arg><option>--batch</option></arg>
<arg><option>-b</option></arg>
</group>
<group>
<arg><option>--clean</option></arg>
<arg><option>-c</option></arg>
</group>
<group>
<arg><option>--expand</option></arg>
<arg><option>-e</option></arg>
</group>
<arg><option>-I <replaceable>dir</replaceable></option></arg>
<group>
<arg><option>--help</option></arg>
<arg><option>-h</option></arg>
</group>
<sbr/>
<group>
<arg><option>--language=<replaceable>lang</replaceable></option></arg>
<arg><option>-l <replaceable>lang</replaceable></option></arg>
</group>
<arg><option>--max-iterations=<replaceable>n</replaceable></option></arg>
<arg><option>--mkidx-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></arg>
<sbr/>
<group>
<arg><option>--pdf</option></arg>
<arg><option>--p</option></arg>
</group>
<group>
<arg><option>--quiet</option></arg>
<arg><option>-q</option></arg>
<arg><option>--silent</option></arg>
<arg><option>-s</option></arg>
</group>
<arg><option>--run-viewer</option></arg>
<arg><option>--src</option></arg>
<sbr/>
<group>
<arg><option>--texinfo=<replaceable>cmd</replaceable></option></arg>
<arg><option>-t=<replaceable>cmd</replaceable></option></arg>
</group>
<arg><option>--tex-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></arg>
<sbr/>
<group>
<arg><option>--version</option></arg>
<arg><option>-v</option></arg>
</group>
<group>
<arg><option>--verbose</option></arg>
<arg><option>-V</option></arg>
</group>
<arg><option>--viewer-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></arg>
<arg choice="plain" rep="repeat"><replaceable>file</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis>

</simplesect>

<simplesect>

<title>Description</title>

<para>&texify; runs &Texinfo; or &LaTeX; input files through &tex;
(&pdftex;) in turn until all cross-references are resolved, building
all indices.</para>

<para>The directory containing each <replaceable>file</replaceable> is
searched for included files.  The suffix of
<replaceable>file</replaceable> is used to determine its language
(&LaTeX; or &Texinfo;).</para>

<para>&makeinfo; is used to perform &Texinfo; macro expansion before
running &tex; when needed.</para>

</simplesect>

<simplesect>

<title>Options</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>-@</option></term>
<listitem><para>Use <markup role="tex">@input</markup> (instead of
<markup role="tex">\input</markup>); for preloaded
&Texinfo;.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--batch</option></term>
<term><option>-b</option></term>
<listitem><para>No
<indexterm>
<primary>--batch</primary>
</indexterm>
interaction.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--clean</option></term>
<term><option>-c</option></term>
<listitem><para>Remove all auxiliary
<indexterm>
<primary>--clean</primary>
</indexterm>
files.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--expand</option></term>
<term><option>-e</option></term>
<listitem><para>Force macro expansion
<indexterm>
<primary>--expand</primary>
</indexterm>
using &makeinfo;.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>-I <replaceable>dir</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Search <replaceable>dir</replaceable> for input files.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--help</option></term>
<term><option>-h</option></term>
<listitem><para>Display help and exit
<indexterm>
<primary>--help</primary>
</indexterm>
successfully.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--language=<replaceable>lang</replaceable></option></term>
<term><option>-l <replaceable>lang</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Specify the language of input files: either
<indexterm>
<primary>--language=lang</primary>
</indexterm>
<varname>latex</varname> or <varname>texinfo</varname>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--max-iterations=<replaceable>n</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Limits the number of iterations to prevent endless
<indexterm>
<primary>-max-iterations=n</primary>
</indexterm>
processing.  The default for
<replaceable>n</replaceable> is <literal>5</literal>.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--mkidx-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Pass <replaceable>option</replaceable>
<indexterm>
<primary>--mkidx-option=option</primary>
</indexterm>
to the index generator.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--pdf</option></term>
<term><option>-p</option></term>
<listitem><para>Use &pdftex; (or
<indexterm>
<primary>--pdf</primary>
</indexterm>
&pdflatex;) for processing.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--quiet</option></term>
<term><option>-q</option></term>
<term><option>--silent</option></term>
<term><option>-s</option></term>
<listitem><para>No screen output unless errors
<indexterm>
<primary>--quiet</primary>
</indexterm>
plies <option>--batch</option>).</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--run-viewer</option></term>
<listitem><para>Run a viewer on
<indexterm>
<primary>--run-viewer</primary>
</indexterm>
the resulting &DVI;
(&PDF;) file.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--src</option></term>
<listitem><para>Pass <option>--src-specials</option> to
<indexterm>
<primary>--src</primary>
</indexterm>
the &TeX; compiler.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--texinfo=<replaceable>cmd</replaceable></option></term>
<term><option>-t=<replaceable>cmd</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Insert <replaceable>cmd</replaceable> after
<indexterm>
<primary>--texinfo=cmd</primary>
</indexterm>
<varname>@setfilename</varname> in copy of input
file.  Multiple values accumulate.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--tex-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Pass
<indexterm>
<primary>--tex-option=option</primary>
</indexterm>
<replaceable>option</replaceable> to the compiler.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--verbose</option></term>
<term><option>-V</option></term>
<listitem><para>Print information on what is
<indexterm>
<primary>--verbose</primary>
</indexterm>
being done.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--version</option></term>
<term><option>-v</option></term>
<listitem>
<para>Display version information and exit
<indexterm>
<primary>--version</primary>
</indexterm>
successfully.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry>
<term><option>--viewer-option=<replaceable>option</replaceable></option></term>
<listitem><para>Pass <replaceable>option</replaceable> to
<indexterm>
<primary>--viewer-option=option</primary>
</indexterm>
the viewer.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</simplesect>

<simplesect>

<title>Environment Variables</title>

<para>The values of the <envar>BIBTEX</envar>, <envar>LATEX</envar>
(or <envar>PDFLATEX</envar>), <envar>MAKEINDEX</envar>,
<envar>MAKEINFO</envar>, <envar>TEX</envar> (or
<envar>PDFTEX</envar>), and <envar>TEXINDEX</envar>
environment variables are used to run those commands, if they are set.</para>

</simplesect>

<simplesect>

<title>Aliases</title>

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term>&texi2dvi;</term>
<listitem><para>Equivalent to &texify;.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</simplesect>

